      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2091: The retry timer is stored as `std::shared_ptr\u003cvoid\u003e` and down-cast with `static_pointer_cast` at each use. This removes type safety and can turn future maintenance mistakes into undefined behavior. Since `jamiaccount.cpp` now includes `asio/steady_timer.hpp`, the header can forward-declare the timer type and store the real type directly.\n```suggestion\nnamespace asio {\nclass steady_timer;\n}\n\nstd::shared_ptr\u003casio::steady_timer\u003e identityRetryTimer_;\n```\nThen the call sites can use `identityRetryTimer_-\u003ecancel()` without casts.",
