      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2098: The retry path captures `w` and then reuses the same weak pointer inside callbacks passed to `startSync`, but the outer lambda resets `identityRetryTimer_` before calling `startSync`. If `startSync` can synchronously invoke one of these callbacks, this is safe, but the ownership/lifetime relationship is non-obvious and fragile. Prefer capturing a local `weakThis` explicitly and avoid reusing the outer capture implicitly.\n```suggestion\nauto weakThis \u003d thisPtr-\u003eweak();\nthisPtr-\u003eaccountManager_-\u003estartSync(\n    [weakThis](const std::shared_ptr\u003cdht::crypto::Certificate\u003e\u0026 crt) {\n        if (auto account \u003d weakThis.lock())\n            account-\u003eonAccountDeviceFound(crt);\n    },\n    [weakThis] {\n        if (auto account \u003d weakThis.lock())\n            account-\u003eonAccountDeviceAnnounced();\n    },\n    thisPtr-\u003epublishPresence_);\n```",
